The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Sourav for national one-dayers
                                                   Sourav for national one-dayers
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Former India captain Sourav Ganguly Wednesday said he was open to playing for Bengal in the domestic one-day tournaments but wouldnt take part in the longer version of the game in the Ranji Trophy.         
	I have plans to play one-day matches for Bengal. It will help me keep fit and get me ready for the next edition of the Indian Premier League (IPL). However, I will not be playing the longer format, Sourav said at a promotional in the city.         
	When asked about his plans for the IPLs third edition, he said, We will see how it goes. and how the Knight Riders think tank plan out the next season.         
	Sourav also shrugged off the controversies surrounding the Knights this time, as he said: There was a controversy in the first edition of the IPL also But dont ask me what it was because then it would be another controversy. With the media getting involved in a much wider range, there will be controversies.                                                                                                                       
